ð18Þ

where L is the total length of the curve or sum of distances between successive points, and d is the diameter estimated as the distance between the ﬁrst point of the sequence and the point of the sequence that provides the farthest distance. Mathematically, d can be expressed as d ¼ max ðkxð1Þ; xðiÞkÞ:

